    • Field Detail

      • CLOSE_TYPE_ARGS

        static final char CLOSE_TYPE_ARGS
        Special character token we use to differentiate '>' as an operator and '>' as the end of the type arguments. The former uses '>' and it requires a preceding whitespace. The latter uses this, and it does not have a preceding whitespace.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • isPrinting

        boolean isPrinting()
        Returns:
        true if we are in the printing mode, where we actually produce text. The other (internal) mode is the "collecting mode".
